text: Corinne Kimball (25 December 1873 in Boston - 1937) was an American actress and singer. She was also a child actress. Her mother Jennie Kimball was an actor and theater manager. She appeared in "Monte Cristo, Jr.," "Queen of the Stage," and "Carmen." == References == Category:1873 births Category:1937 deaths Category:American stage actors Category:Actors from Boston Category:Singers from Boston
